Ctrl + c
this command is useful in two situations:
1- when a command is running an I wanna kill it.
2- when I'm typing a command in the terminal and I wanna go to a clean line without executing what I already typed.

Ctrl + a
when I'm typing a command in the  terminal, I can use this shortcut to jump to the start of the line

Ctr + e
when I'm typing a command in the  terminal, I can use this shortcut to jump to the end of the line

Alt + f & Alt + b
when typing a command on the terminal, I can use these shortcuts to jump one word Forward or Backward.



